public interface NamedObject
An object with a programmatic name. An object that is a NamedObject differs from an object that is Named in that its name is meant for use by programmers and not end users. If objectName() is not implemented, a synthetic name for the object is created with syntheticName(Object).

jonathanl (shibo)

      default String objectName()
      Returns:
      The name of this object for use in programming and debugging. If this method is not overridden, the name will be the simple class name in hyphenated form followed by this object's identity hash code in hexadecimal.
